djoint operators generated by their\ncorresponding second-order differential expressions in appropriate Hilbert\nspaces. In addition, we present a new Type III family of $X_{m}$-Laguerre\npolynomials along with a detailed disquisition of its properties. We include\nseveral representations of these polynomials, orthogonality, norms,\ncompleteness, the location of their local extrema and roots, root asymptotics,\nas well as the spectral study of the second-order Type III exceptional\n$X_{m}$-Laguerre differential expression.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Jul 2014 20:50:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-24"}
