perature dependence of water reorientation is\nlargely independent of the confinement size and described by an Arrhenius law\nwith an activation energy of $E_a\\!\\approx\\!0.5\\ $eV in the low-temperature\nrange, $T\\!<\\!180 $K, revealing that the confinement size plays a minor role\nfor the $\\beta$ process of water.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Jul 2014 09:38:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
